        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. This number was scaled from the US productio volume 2005 (6000000000kg). Refrence(s): American Chemical Society. 2006. Production: Growth is the Norm. Chemical and Engineering News. 84 (28): 59–68. July 10, 2006. Online: http://pubs.acs.org/doi/pdf/10.1021/cen-v084n028.p059, accessed 29 June 2017

The Global production volume is estimated based on information from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council) and the American Chemistry Council. 
According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3,534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (USA, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the USA total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 
The Global production volume is calculated based on the sales share from the USA share of sales 14.7%. 

Reference(s):
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html</productionVolumeComment>
