In this process nitric oxide is oxidized with ammonia at 750-900°C (usually 850°C) under the presence of a platinum catalyst (Thiemann et al., 2000). This is a strongly exothermic reaction, and can therefore serve as a heat source. The process efficiency is 93 – 98% (Thiemann et al., 2000), here we use 95%.
Chemical Reaction:
4 NH3 + 5 O2 → 4 ·NO + 6 H2O</comment>
